.TH shell 1 "February 23, 2022" "Holberton School 0x16 - C" "shell man page"

.SH NAME

.B hsh \- a custom command language interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS

.B ./hsh [command_file] [argument...]

.SH DESCRIPTION

The hsh utilitiy is a command language interpreter that shall execute commands read from a command line string, the standard input, or a specified file.

.SH OPTIONS

.SH OPERANDS

.SH STDIN

.SH INPUT FILES

.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES

.SH STDOUT

.SH STDERR

.SH OUTPUT FILES

.SH EXTENDED DESCRIPTION

.SH EXIT STATUS

.SH APPLICATION USAGE

The standard input and the standard error are the files that determine whether a shell is interactive when \fB-i\fR is not specified. For example:
